         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">June 22 /72. ¶ My dear Baron ¶  ¶ I have several letters to thank you for, which I shall now proceed to discuss. ¶  ¶ I have already informed you of the safe arrival of the noble Tree Ferns &amp; of our h...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">72.06.22</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">From Joseph Hooker</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">RB MSS M3, Library, Royal Botanic Gardens Melbourne.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Letter bears the embossed emblem: 'Royal Gardens Kew'.</p>
               </note>June 22 /72.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">My dear Baron</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have several letters to thank you for, which I shall now proceed to discuss.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I have already informed you of the safe arrival of the noble Tree Ferns &amp; of our having seen to their despatch to their destinations.<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">J. Hooker to M, April 1872 (in this edition as 72-04-00)?</p>
               </note> The noble <name key="Dicksonia">Dicksonia</name> you have given us is pushing fronds. The <name key="Alsophila">Alsophila</name> not yet but we do not despair of it. It is covered with a light canvas petticoat! to keep its flanks moist &amp; stored in the most favorable place for growth.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Our <name key="Dicksonia">Dicksonia</name>s are the wonders of the world, all owing to my never allowing a dead frond to be removed — &amp; the great <name key="Todea">Todea</name> retains its luxuriance, it having now some 300 fronds on it, wholly through my treatment. I have it stood in a shallow pan, surrounded with blocks of stone &amp; ferns, backed by a layer of soil confined by cask staves.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I hope that you have passed your <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">ordeal</hi>
               </seg>. I am far from the end of mine — Gladstone supports that Ayrton through thick &amp; thin, &amp; my friends are hitherto foiled in their attempts to get my correspondence which has been called for in <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">both Houses</hi>
               </seg> of Parliament. The enclosed address will reveal to you my position, &amp; so I need say no more.<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Following this letter in the file are cuttings from <seg style="font-style: italic; ">The Times</seg>, 30 July and 9 August 1872, reporting the progress of Hooker's dispute with A. S. Ayrton, Chief Commissioner of Works. However, it is clear from the dates that these are not the address to which Hooker refers. See also MacLeod (1974).</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I shall take care that when you send me the live plants named after the D. of Buckingham (whose name I forget) arrive to send his Graces Gardener their share.<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 1 March 1872.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I am delighted to hear that you have more Chatham Island plants, but disappointed that they contain no more novelty.<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 24 April 1872 (in this edition as 72-04-24a).</p>
               </note> Will no one ever go to Antipodes Bounty<note xml:id="ftn6" type="footnote" n="6">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Sub-Antarctic island groups south of the Chatham Islands.</p>
               </note> &amp; Emerald Islands<note xml:id="ftn7" type="footnote" n="7">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">A phantom island south of Macquarie Island, reported by a British sealing ship in 1821 but not found by subsequent searchers.</p>
               </note>?</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>I enclose Mr Baker's answer about the Fern.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>We have just lost Mr Kingston a very active assistant in the Herbarium, who has died of the rupture of a blood-vessel in the Lungs.<note xml:id="ftn8" type="footnote" n="8">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">R. C. Kingston died on 21 June 1872.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Thanks for the note about arillate <name key="Tiliaceae">Tiliaceae</name>
               <note xml:id="ftn9" type="footnote" n="9">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See M to J. Hooker, 23 March 1872.</p>
               </note> — a fact I knew well having often examined the aril of I think <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Echinocarpus">Echinocarpus</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> in India — I cannot tell how I allowed such an oversight to pass in the Gen. Plant.<note xml:id="ftn10" type="footnote" n="10">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Bentham &amp; Hooker (1862-83), vol. 1, p. 228.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>The <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">
                     <name key="Rubiaceae">Rubiaceae</name>
                  </hi>
               </seg> went to press today, but will take some months to print — we can verify <seg style="">
                  <hi rend="underline">every quotation</hi>
               </seg> in the proof as well as Mss. from the works themselves.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Bentham has finished the <name key="Euphorbiaceae">Euphorbiaceae</name> for the Australian Flora &amp; is now at <name key="Calycereae">Calycereae</name> for Gen. Plant. — the <name key="Compositae">Compositae</name> are all ready for press.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Can you send us your species of <name key="Hymenophyllum">Hymenophyllum</name>?<note xml:id="ftn11" type="footnote" n="11">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">See also J. Hooker to M, April 1872 (in this edition as 72-04-00).</p>
               </note> The best way is to establish them on billets of Tree fern &amp; nail them to the top of a Ward's case of plants.</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Ever very sincerely yr</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Jos D. Hooker</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
